  "title": "Regional Manager #81760",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Manufacturing/ Food Production</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Regional Manager</strong></li><li>Working Location: Senoko</li><li>Working Hours: 5.5 days (Mon – Fri, 8am – 5pm; Sat, 8am – 12pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic $6,000 - $7,000 + Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Outlet & Operations Management: Manage day-to-day operations across assigned outlets to ensure smooth and consistent service.</li><li>Work closely with on-site teams to build good working relationships and maintain consistent operating standards.</li><li>Ensure outlets follow company SOPs, food quality standards, and service guidelines.</li><li>Sales Performance & Cost Control: Meet sales targets while controlling costs effectively.</li><li>Monitor outlet results and prepare routine/monthly sales reports, with suggestions to improve performance.</li><li>People Leadership & Manpower Planning: Plan staffing needs, deploy staff, and manage productivity.</li><li>Track staff performance and conduct performance reviews.</li><li>Coach and support teams to meet sales targets and provide good customer service.</li><li>Food Safety, Hygiene & Compliance: Maintain hygiene, cleanliness, and food safety standards across all assigned outlets.</li><li>Ensure outlets comply with Singapore Food Agency (SFA) requirements and other relevant regulations.</li><li>Carry out other duties or projects assigned by the Director.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>At least 5 years of relevant experience in F&B operations, preferably managing multiple outlets (e.g., casual dining or hotpot).</li><li>Strong leadership, communication, and interpersonal skills.</li><li>Good understanding of Singapore’s food safety and regulatory requirements.</li><li>Good financial knowledge, including profit and loss (P&L) management.</li><li>Able to work well in a fast-paced environment.</li><li>Proficient in English; ability to communicate with Mandarin-speaking stakeholders for work purposes is an advantage.</li><li>Willing to travel when required.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#81760 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
